{"name":"Resist Cold or Heat","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric repels the chilling effects of cold or heat, protecting himself and others. He can withstand such conditions without discomfort. When casting the spell, the cleric chooses which effect to resist (heat or cold). It is possible to cast the spell twice and create a resistance to both effects.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Resist Cold or Heat]{Resist Cold or Heat}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Self or more","duration":"1 round or more","page":"266","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Resist Cold or Heat","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/burning-passion.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2VloquJ75SeRT4jB"}
{"name":"Second Sight","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Using sortilege, haruspicy, or some other method appropriate to the cleric, he augurs the future. In doing so, the cleric gains insight about the consequences his actions will bring.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Second Sight]{Second Sight}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Self","duration":"1 round or more","page":"267","castingTime":"1 turn","results":{"table":"Second Sight","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/octogonal-eye.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4ZrsYz55lqwKluhB"}
{"_id":"NSCBFUtZtwzTeVi0","name":"Paralysis","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The light of the cleric&rsquo;s deity prevents his enemies from raising a hand to perform baleful deeds.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Paralysis]{Paralysis}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Touch or more","duration":"1 round or more","page":"264","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Paralysis","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Will save vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/pause-button.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Food of the Gods","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric calls upon the power of his deity to feed the masses. This spell either makes inedible food edible or magically creates viands when no other food and drink is available. Magically-created food is a spongy, grey, and bland-tasting substance that spoils after 24 hours. Magically-created water is clean rainwater that remains drinkable for as long as it is properly stored.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Food of the Gods]{Food of the Gods}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"30","duration":"24 hours (see below)","page":"262","castingTime":"1 turn","results":{"table":"Food of the Gods","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/cornucopia.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bgF2yS1JgdheNQx2"}
{"_id":"dGgjrqZdOlxyc5Im","name":"Detect Evil","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric holds up his holy symbol and detects emanations of evil within a ray that extends straight out 5&rsquo; wide and 60&rsquo; (or more) ahead of the symbol. The definition of &ldquo;evil&rdquo; is based on the cleric: generally it encompasses creatures of opposed alignment, those unholy to the cleric&rsquo;s deity, and those with clearly harmful intent. Depending on the strength of the spell, it may detect even more subtle dangers. This spell does not reveal creatures that are otherwise hidden but does inform the cleric that evil intentions radiate from a certain position. This spell may be reversed to detect good, which means creatures of allied alignment, common deity, or similar holy goals.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Evil]{Detect Evil}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"60 radius from cleric or more (see below)","duration":"6 turns","page":"259","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Detect Evil","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/spyglass.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Blessing Object","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric beseeches the blessing of his god. If bestowed, this blessing can be a great boon to the success of his endeavors. The spell can be cast on the cleric himself, on an object, or on one of the cleric&rsquo;s allies.</p>\n<p>The spell is most effective on allies with the same alignment. Casting this spell on a target with a different alignment incurs a -1 penalty to the spell check, and casting the spell on a target with an opposite alignment or in allegiance to an opposed deity incurs a -2 penalty.</p>\n<p>The casting time reflects prayer and meditation as the cleric uses his holy symbol to conduct the blessing ritual. Blessings cast under auspicious circumstances receive a bonus of +1 to +4, according to the judge&rsquo;s discretion. Such circumstances include casting in the temple of the cleric&rsquo;s god, casting on a sacred holiday, or casting with the use of a holy relic. Likewise, casting under inauspicious circumstances, such as in an unholy enemy temple, receives a penalty ranging from -1 to -4.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Blessing Object]{Blessing Object}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Self or touch","duration":"1 turn or more","page":"255","castingTime":"1 action or more (see below)","results":{"table":"Blessing Object","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/holy-water.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ev6n0wLDHb95pYFx"}
{"_id":"exOH9jdlpBuKuwSC","name":"Blessing","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Counts as @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-cleric-1.Blessing Self]{Blessing Self}, @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-cleric-1.Blessing Ally]{Blessing Ally}, and @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-cleric-1.Blessing Object]{Blessing Object}.</p>\n<p>The cleric beseeches the blessing of his god. If bestowed, this blessing can be a great boon to the success of his endeavors. The spell can be cast on the cleric himself, on an object, or on one of the cleric&rsquo;s allies.</p>\n<p>The spell is most effective on allies with the same alignment. Casting this spell on a target with a different alignment incurs a -1 penalty to the spell check, and casting the spell on a target with an opposite alignment or in allegiance to an opposed deity incurs a -2 penalty.</p>\n<p>The casting time reflects prayer and meditation as the cleric uses his holy symbol to conduct the blessing ritual. Blessings cast under auspicious circumstances receive a bonus of +1 to +4, according to the judge&rsquo;s discretion. Such circumstances include casting in the temple of the cleric&rsquo;s god, casting on a sacred holiday, or casting with the use of a holy relic. Likewise, casting under inauspicious circumstances, such as in an unholy enemy temple, receives a penalty ranging from -1 to -4.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Blessing]{Blessing}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"","duration":"","page":"255","castingTime":"","results":{"table":"Blessing","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/holy-water.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Protection from Evil","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric calls upon his deity to protect him from harm. He is protected even if he is not aware of the danger. The definition of &ldquo;evil&rdquo; is based on the cleric: generally it encompasses creatures of opposed alignment, those unholy to the cleric&rsquo;s deity, and those with clear harmful intent. Depending on the strength of the spell, it may detect even more subtle dangers. This spell may be reversed to protect from good.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Protection from Evil]{Protection from Evil}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Self or more","duration":"1 turn per CL","page":"265","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Protection from Evil","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Varies","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/evil-moon.svg","effects":[],"_id":"io9KLzOlp37Ip1iK"}
{"_id":"j4eIaoEtJARt7poD","name":"Holy Sanctuary","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric invokes a place of sanctuary where he and his allies are safe from harm.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Holy Sanctuary]{Holy Sanctuary}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"Self or more","duration":"1 round or more","page":"263","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Holy Sanctuary","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Will save vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/laurels.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Word of Command","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric speaks a powerful word that carries with it the commanding will of his deity. Creatures hearing the word are bound to obey. The word must be a single word, which must describe an action. For example, &ldquo;go,&rdquo; &ldquo;attack,&rdquo; &ldquo;retreat,&rdquo; &ldquo;speak,&rdquo; &ldquo;swim,&rdquo; &ldquo;grovel,&rdquo; &ldquo;silence,&rdquo; and so on. The word must be spoken in the direction of a single sentient target within range. That target receives a Will save to resist; if failed, it must obey the command for its next round. The command is interpreted by the creature&rsquo;s natural thought processes; e.g., issuing an &ldquo;attack&rdquo; command to an herbivore may have a different response than to a carnivore. The word of command cannot be longer in length than a single word and may be subject to misinterpretation. If the command is completely contrary to a creature&rsquo;s natural instinct, it receives a +4 bonus to its Will save to resist; for example, commanding a desert lizard to &ldquo;swim&rdquo; or any command of &ldquo;suicide.&rdquo;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Word of Command]{Word of Command}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"30 or more","duration":"1 round or more","page":"268","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Word of Command","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Will save vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/lightning-shout.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jXLluQBIMXwMioMe"}
{"name":"Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric extinguishes the light of the sun, demonstrating the great power of his deity. From a distance, the darkness appears to be a space of deepest night; no light will penetrate it. Creatures within are blinded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Darkness]{Darkness}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"20 radius or more","duration":"1 turn or more","page":"258","castingTime":"1 action or more","results":{"table":"Darkness","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/plain-square_invert.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kDozeUOVt4lgliyv"}
{"_id":"oeA9CgQLa6vBVA3c","name":"Detect Magic","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric knows if there has been an enchantment laid upon a person, place or thing within range. The range is a cone, 30&rsquo; long and 30&rsquo; wide at its end, emanating from the cleric&rsquo;s holy symbol.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Magic]{Detect Magic}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"30 or more","duration":"2 turns","page":"260","castingTime":"2 actions","results":{"table":"Detect Magic","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-cleric"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/magic-swirl.svg","effects":[]}
